{
  "text": "All right. And saying that the Queen's Chamber was the initiatory place. Could you tell me what you mean by that? I am this question is a large one. We cannot describe initiation in its pacific sense, due to our distortion towards the belief understanding that the process which we offered so many of your years ago was not a balanced one. However you are aware of the concept of initiation and realize that it demands the centering of the being upon the seeking of the Creator. We have hoped to balance this understanding by enunciating the law of one that is that all things are one creator. Thus seeking the Creator is done not just in meditation and the work of an adept, but in the experiential nexus of each moment the initiation of Queen's Chamber has to do with the abandoning of self to such desire to know the Creator in full that the purified in streaming light is drawn in balance fashion through all energy centers, meeting in indigo and opening the gate to intelligent infinity. Thus the entity experiences true life or as your people call it resurrection.",
